(3) Transportation Around Japan

For most long distance travel in Japan, trains are often the best
choice.  There are also busses, planes, and ferries, but in most cases
the trains are faster, cheaper, and more frequent.

In Tokyo, as well as some other cities, it often pays to buy a full
day subway ticket.  One contributer writes that in Tokyo, an all day
pass runs about the same as three one way tickets.  Prices are
reported on the ticket machines - in Japanese.  [I've never bought
one, so no more details yet - ed]

