(7) Emergencies

Phone Numbers: The phone number to call an ambulance or fire truck (or
just report disaster) is 119. This is a free of charge number. You
just push the emergency button (it's red) at the bottom of the phone
and dial. The number for the police is also free of charge - it is
110. It's doubtful the person on the other end will speak any language
other than Japanese.

For directory assistance the number is 104, but you have to pay for
this one. Usually for one number they charge you 30 yen. If you are
using a telephone card the 30 yen is deducted automatically.

Police are generally pretty helpful. If you get lost, a police box -
they're everywhere in cities - is a good place to ask for directions.
If I arrived in some out of the way place totally at a loss where to
find a place to stay, I'd probably ask at the local police station.


@ENDNODE

